Wasn’t expecting much… but this one surprised me.

Tried the LAKMĒ Perfect Radiance Serum with 7% niacinamide for 7 days.

Day 1: Dark spots felt pretty stubborn.
Day 3: Skin looked a little calmer.
Day 5: Spots started fading.
Day 7: A more even, quiet kind of glow.

Not dramatic, just gentle, visible progress.

@lakmeskin

If I could sit beside my younger self—even for a moment—I wouldn’t change her. I’d just hold her hand a little tighter and whisper the things she never got to hear.

I’d tell her that it’s okay to feel too much, to cry when no one’s watching, and to not always be okay. That the world will try to quiet her softness, but that softness will be her strength.

I’d tell her that not everyone will stay, and that’s not her fault. Some people leave to make space for the ones who truly see her—the ones who won’t just love the light in her, but also the shadows.

I’d tell her that the dreams she holds secretly in her heart? They’re not too big. She’s not too much. She’s just right—and she’ll get there, step by brave little step.

I’d remind her that healing isn’t linear, that growth feels lonely sometimes, and that even when she doesn’t recognize the person in the mirror, she’s becoming someone beautiful—someone real.

And most of all, I’d say this:

You’re going to be okay. You’re going to bloom in places you once felt buried. You’ll find peace, even in pieces. You’ll look back one day and realize—you didn’t just survive, you became.

So here’s to her.
The girl who kept going.
The girl I still carry with me. 🤍
